item.description:
CLIMB, SWIM, AND BOAT ALL W/ OUT MOVING YOUR CAR! Pawtuckaway is a well known climbing area w/ lots to discover if you've never been.
May be buggy so BRING THE BUG STUFF!
Directions for those who will be still coming: You don't go to the big lake side of Pawtuckaway!
From 101 take Raymond exit to 107 go right if coming from East. Follow 107 to light Past all the stores (end of road) Take a left on 27 W follow for mile or so You will pass a sign for 156 and Pawtuck. (don't take this road!) continue on 27 bear right on 107. Mile or so on right is Revservation rd. Down a bit the road turns to dirt, and may be bumpy. there will be a fork in the road, go right. When you see a left turn w/ an open gate turn, follow this road until round pond. Going straight through the intersection. If you pass the "short cut" you will pass tthe Tower trail and loop around to the intersection and go right to round pond.
item.how_to_find_us: Look for the Large green van, meetup signs. We will start on LakeSide Jam near round pond, can see the cliff from the parking.
item.why: Pawtuckaway has many climbs, both short top rope or bouldering. There is a place to swim on round pond. Easy access to kayak/canoe also.
item.name: Pawtuckaway Outing
